Dassault Aviation, EDF, GDF Suez, Total: French Equity Preview

-- B y   H e a t h e r   S m i t h
-- 
2011-07-11T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-10/dassault-aviation-edf-gdf-suez-total-french-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share prices are
from the last close.  France’s  CAC 40 Index (CAC)  fell 1.7 percent to 3,913.55 in
Paris. The  SBF 120 Index (SBF120)  declined 1.5 percent.  Dassault Aviation SA (AM)  : Brazil will delay a decision
on a $5 billion order for new fighter jets to next year, the
country’s Defense Minister Nelson Azevedo Jobim said July 9.
Dassault is promoting its Rafale against Boeing Co.’s F/A-18
Super Hornet and Sweden’s Saab AB’s Gripen. The shares rose 0.2
percent to 701.50 euros.  Electricite de France SA (EDF FP):  Europe ’s biggest power
utility is preparing to order 44 replacement steam generators
for its nuclear power plants, and French supplier Areva SA will
get about two-thirds of the order, the newspaper Le Figaro
reported, without saying where it got the information. The
shares dropped 2 percent to 26.80 euros.  GDF Suez (GSZ)  SA: Europe’s largest gas network operator
is discussing cooperation with Gazprom OAO, including on the
Nord Stream natural gas pipeline, the company said in a
statement on July 8. The shares fell 2.4 percent to 24.29 euros.  Remy Cointreau SA (RCO)  : The maker of Remy Martin cognac
completed the sale of its Piper-Heidsieck Compagnie Champenoise
champagne unit to EPI Group, according to a statement. Shares
gained 0.1 percent to 59.04 euros.  Total SA (FP)  : Europe’s largest oil refiner must raise
its prices as market prices rise, Chief Executive Officer
Christophe de Margerie said at an event in Aix-en-Provence.
Total is no longer in exclusive discussions to sell its Lindsey
refinery in the U.K. and there are several bidders involved in
the process, delaying the sale process, he said. Shares fell 1.1
percent to 39.97 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Heather Smith in Paris at 
 hsmith26@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@Bloomberg.net . 